                <fr:title text="Monotone Sequence">Monotone Sequence</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A sequence is increasing if for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_n\leq  a_{n+1}]]></fr:tex>. A sequence is decreasing if for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_n\geq  a_{n+1}]]></fr:tex>. A sequence is <html:strong>monotone</html:strong> if it is either increasing or decreasing.</html:p>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors />
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>4</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>23</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:title text="Monotone Convergence Theorem">Monotone Convergence Theorem</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>If a sequence is monotone and bounded, then it <fr:link href="/forest/001F/" title="Convergent Sequence" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/001F/" display-uri="001F" type="local">converges</fr:link>.</html:p>
                    <html:p>For an increasing sequence, this statement follows from the fact that we have a supremum and we can use the monotone condition to show that
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[|a_n-s|<\epsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>4</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>23</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/001K/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>001K</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/forest/001K/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Convergent Series">Convergent Series</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>We can write an infinite series as,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\sum _{n=1}^{\infty }b_n = b_1+b_2+b_3+\dots ]]></fr:tex>
We define the sequence of partial sums <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(s_m)]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[s_m=b_1+\dots +b_m]]></fr:tex>
The infinite series coverges to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if the sequence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(s_m)]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="/forest/001F/" title="Convergent Sequence" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/001F/" display-uri="001F" type="local">converges</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors />
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>4</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>23</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:title text="Cauchy Condensation Test">Cauchy Condensation Test</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(b_n)]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/forest/001J/" title="Monotone Sequence" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/001J/" display-uri="001J" type="local">decreasing sequence</fr:link> and satisfies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b_n\geq  0]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>. The the series <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sum _{n=1}^\infty  b_n]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="/forest/001K/" title="Convergent Series" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/001K/" display-uri="001K" type="local">converges</fr:link> if and only if
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\sum _{n=0}^\infty  2^n b_{2^n}]]></fr:tex>
Also converges.
</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
